==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tenuis
<hw>Ten"u*is</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Tenues</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>tenuis</ets> fine, thin. See <er>Tenuous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Gr.
Gram.)</fld> <def>One of the three surd mutes ⟦kappa⟧, ⟦pi⟧, ⟦tau⟧; --
so called in relation to their respective middle letters, or medials,
⟦gamma⟧, ⟦beta⟧, ⟦delta⟧, and their aspirates, ⟦chi⟧, ⟦phi⟧, ⟦theta⟧.
The term is also applied to the corresponding letters and articulate
elements in other languages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tenuity</ent>⟦br⟧
